title: 'Bising' maintains speed; moderate to heavy rains expected

organizations.name: philippine atmospheric, geophysical and astronomical services administration

text: 'Bising' maintains speed; moderate to heavy rains expected (philstar.com)   11:16am Track of "Bising" as of 10 a.m. Sunday, February 5. PAGASA/Released MANILA, Philippines â€” Tropical Depression Bising has maintained speed and continues to move in a north-northwest direction. In its 11 a.m. severe weather bulletin on Sunday, the Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration (PAGASA) said that "Bising" is expected to bring an estimated moderate to heavy rainfall within its 300 km diameter. PAGASA also warned against sea travel over the eastern seaboard of southern Luzon, Visayas and Mindanao. RELATED: ' Bising ' to bring rains to Visayas-Mindanao As of 10 a.m., the state weather bureau said the center of the tropical depression was estimated at 400 km east of Surigao City, Surigao del Norte. It packs maximum winds of up to 45 kph near the center and gustiness of up to 55 kph. "Bising" is forecast to move north northwest at 11 kph. Forecast positions 24 hours (Tomorrow morning): 450 km east of Borongan City, Eastern Samar 48 hours (Tuesday morning): 690 km east-northeast of Borongan City, Eastern Samar 72 hours (Wednesday morning): 905 km east-northeast of Borongan City, Eastern Samar 96 hours (Thursday morning): 1,065 km east-northeast of Borongan City, Eastern Samar No tropical cyclone warning signal is raised.
